ğŸ› ï¸ Implementation Details
1ï¸âƒ£ Managed Delta Table Creation

Cleaned Silver-layer data was written as a managed Delta table using saveAsTable.
This allows Databricks to manage both metadata and storage.

silver_df.write.format("delta") \
    .mode("overwrite") \
    .saveAsTable("events_table")

2ï¸âƒ£ Querying the Managed Table
SELECT * FROM events_table LIMIT 5;


This confirms that the table is registered and accessible using SQL.

3ï¸âƒ£ Views for Controlled Access

To simulate governance and restricted access, a view was created exposing only selected columns.

CREATE OR REPLACE VIEW events_public AS
SELECT
    event_time,
    event_type,
    category_code,
    price
FROM events_table;


Views help ensure that sensitive data remains hidden while still enabling analytics.

4ï¸âƒ£ Access Control (Conceptual)

Although permissions were not executed directly, the correct syntax and purpose were studied:

-- Example (Production Environment)
GRANT SELECT
ON TABLE ecommerce_catalog.sales.events
TO analyst_role;

ğŸ“˜ Key Takeaways

Governance is a critical part of data engineering

